<br>
Yeah! First off, the lines. :) General form and proportion is pretty nice, I like! :) What program did you use to do the lines with though? 'cos a program like Illustrator would rule at doing stuff like that, with bezier curves and stuff. It looks like you've used some kind of straightline/vector tool there, see if there's a bezier setting so you can fool around with curves and stuff, there are a lot of flat edges in there that imo wouldlook better curved. :) Also, it could do with some linewidth variation. line widths can be used to emphasise space, shape and shadow; for example, space: if a line starts far away from you and finishes closer, it would get thicker as it got nearer. This means that objects nearest would also have thicker outlines. shape: the line can be varied along a curve to help emphasise it's curviness. :D For example, it can start off thin, get thicker in the middle, and taper off again. Also, thicker lines can be used to convey bulkiness/mass.  shadow: Lines in shadow can be thicker. Typically (uh, in western comics, anyway) the lightsource is normally defined in the inking stage, and heavy shadows are rendered in ink. You lines look a bit flat at the inking stage, maybe a lot of the darkness and shape should have been defined there instead of in the CG. It's your call though; different inking techniques apply to different people, you'll find yourself working well with some techs and not so much with others. :) It's kinda hard to do all of them at once. XD<br>
<br>
Colour! Looks cool. :) I like the lighter one best, there's more variation. The dark one's a bit....black. :D I dig the texturing on his armour too, nice. :) A bit of a beef with the gun though (this could be a lineart issue); it looks like the back of the gun goes on the other side of his right arm. This look kinda unnatural, 'cos he'd have less room to maneuver it than if he had it between both arms. That way he could use both, and you could get some real nice neon reflections going on on there. :) But yeah, it's cool, I like! ^^ *gives cookie* <p><div align="center">
